       <h3>Current Work</h3>
The existing work carried out by George Jose is being reviewed. Source localization and beamforming was applied to existing TCS 
recordings. We initially take forward this work for a scenario of non-overlapping speakers. For illustration, 
sound files of a recorded non-overlapping speaker and it's beamformed output is given:
<div>
<audio controls>
   
  <source src="Spk1_MA_NO.wav" type="audio/wav">
</audio>  
Recorded speaker
 <audio controls>

  <source src="DSB_Spk1.wav" type="audio/wav" >
</audio>
DSB-beamformed 
</div>
ASR needs to be performed to compare these methods with respect to the obtained word error rate (WER).
Post filtering was done on mono-channel .wav files by considering a channel of the arrayed recording.     
After obtaining the ASR results for the recordings being shared, the following  needs to be updated:
